    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Circle of Fifths is a visual diagram that organizes all 12 musical keys in a circle, showing the relationship between tonic notes (key centers) and their relative major and minor keys. To use it for key signatures, start by moving clockwise from C or G to count how many sharps appear (a minor key has the same sharps as its relative major), or move counter-clockwise from C or FA to count flats to find the key. By simply locating your theoretical tonic on the diagram, you can instantly read the specific set of sharp or flat notes required for that key without memorizing scales.",
